# Phase 11A – Core Modules Completion
## GastroERP Backend
### Objective
Complete all missing functionality inside the **existing modules** before introducing any new business domains (POS, CRM, Finance, etc.).

---

# General Rules

You are the Lead Software Architect of the GastroERP project.

The solution already follows:

- Clean Architecture
- Domain Driven Design (DDD)
- CQRS
- MediatR
- Repository Pattern
- Unit of Work
- FluentValidation
- AutoMapper
- ASP.NET Core .NET 9
- SQL Server
- Multi-Tenancy
- JWT Authentication

## IMPORTANT RULES

- Do NOT change the architecture.
- Do NOT introduce another pattern.
- Follow existing project conventions.
- Maintain backward compatibility.
- Preserve Multi-Tenant support.
- Preserve Branch isolation.
- Every new feature must support:
  - TenantId
  - BranchId (when applicable)
  - Audit Fields
  - Soft Delete
  - Concurrency (RowVersion)

---

# Phase Goal

Before implementing any new modules (POS, Finance, CRM...),

the existing modules must become feature-complete.

Modules included:

1. Identity
2. Organization
3. Menu
4. Inventory
5. System Settings

